A fourteen-sided figure, composed using $1 \text{ cm}\times 1 \text{ cm}$ grid squares, is constructed as shown below. What is the area of the figure in $\text{cm}^2$?
{{DGM:26ff336e6b8892a9}}
$\textbf{(A) } 15 \qquad \textbf{(B) } 15.5 \qquad \textbf{(C) } 16 \qquad \textbf{(D) } 16.5 \qquad \textbf{(E) } 17$

A dart board is a regular hexagon divided into regions as shown below. Suppose a dart thrown at the board is equally likely to land anywhere on the board. What is the probability that the dart lands within the center square?
{{DGM:586208de078cf27b}}
$\textbf{(A)}\ \frac{1}{2} \qquad \textbf{(B)}\ \frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} \qquad \textbf{(C)}\ \frac{1}{3} \qquad \textbf{(D)}\ \frac{1}{2\sqrt{3}} \qquad \textbf{(E)}\ \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}$
